      • createVisit

        public static Visit createVisit(Patient patient,
                java.lang.String initVitalStr,
                java.lang.String arrivalDateStr)
                         throws java.lang.Exception
        Creates a new Visit object and adds it visitPool with the lowest unused visit ID, lastVisitID.
        Parameters:
        person - The Person object associated with the Visit.
        initVitalStr - A string representation of the initial vitals, as reported by a nurse.
        arrivalDate - An auto-generated(?) date string of the form "yyyy-mm-dd hh:mm:ss" (24-hr). Note: we might consider just using arrivalDate if we can pass a Date object from the GUI.
        Returns:
        the created Visit object.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - Throws when Visit() instantiation rejects an argument.
